<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-990] setHint should return IllegalArgumentException for invalid query/lock timeout values</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-990</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;JPA2 public draft spec section 3.6.1 Query Interface notes that Query.setHint() should throw a IllegalArgumentException if a supplied hint value is not valid for a given implementation.&lt;br/&gt;
For lock/query timeout, any user supplied value &amp;lt; -1 is invalid and should throw an exception, which is not occurring.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12417316">OPENJPA-990</key>
            <summary>setHint should return IllegalArgumentException for invalid query/lock timeout values</summary>
